description:
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I help to make a difference!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you collaborative, caring and compassionate?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prisons are one of the most challenging, yet rewarding places for healthcare professionals to work - if you’re looking for a role where you can develop your existing skills and learn something new every day, then this is the place to be.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Practice Plus Group are Health in Justice Market leader, providing healthcare services to offenders across the country. Our model of care is our Wellbeing Approach – an integrated, comprehensive approach in recognition of the fact prisoners are a socially-excluded group with healthcare needs which are complex and often associated with poor outcomes. It adopts the premise no single health/wellbeing factor can be taken in isolation of other motivational issues which might impact a person’s care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HMP Hewell is a closed category B male remand prison, with an operational capacity of 1,104. In the main closed site, there are 6 main house block residential units. The prison is operated by Her Majesty’s Prison Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer training and development in our friendly and supportive teams as well as a range of other employee benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So what do we have to offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Receive an annual salary of up to £46,000 per annum - depending on experience, for a full-time role (37.5 hours per week) working across Monday to Friday.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; You&#39;ll also get a number of benefits including a company contributory pension scheme, 25 days annual leave plus 8 public bank holidays pro-rata, plus CPD and study leave.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Other benefits include cycle to work scheme plus training and clinical development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Onsite benefits at HMP Hewell include access to an onsite gym and free parking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A bit about the job...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; As the Deputy Head of Healthcare you will be responsible for the effective day-to-day operational management of all clinical services across the prison. You will manage service level agreements, ensuring performance-monitoring standards are adhered to and the highest standards of care are maintained. You will also be responsible for ensuring compliance with the essential standards of quality and safety.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; You will also be deputising for the Head of Healthcare in their absence and supporting them across the range of their duties. This is a unique opportunity to provide operational management support within the Prison setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A little bit about you...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications welcome from those with a nursing background or a non-clinical operational management background. Either of these must have been a Senior Management Level, due to the complexity of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to provide evidence of your leadership ability and will have undertaken management training, with an understanding of clinical governance and staff management. You will have an awareness of risk assessment and managing budgets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It goes without saying that you’ll have a solid understanding of health and safety, will be self-motivated and able to work autonomously, you’ll show plenty of initiative when it comes to handling a wide range of situations.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Beyond that, you should have a flexible approach and the ability to achieve changing priorities by managing your own time and be an excellent team member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Further Information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; This is a full-time vacancy, working 37.5 hour per week across Monday to Friday.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; An informal site visit may be possible to be arranged, please contact us on the details provided or for an informal chat about the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Face-to-face interviews are due to be held on 16th November at our Midlands Regional Office. This is subject to change and should you be successfully shortlisted for this opportunity Amelia will confirm interview details closer to the date.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Please note that offers of employment are subject to Practice Plus Group Terms &amp; Conditions and enhanced DBS check, references and prison vetting.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; At Practice Plus Group, we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
